properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first/inaugural powered flight over the English channel on July 25, 1909, in Paris, France, by Louis Bleriot with Bleriot XI monoplane; commemorative cancellation stamp dated July 25, 1984 in Paris; includes information on reverse.
